        <Parent_String>strainers (culinary tools) [300201087], culinary tools for separating [300207596], culinary equipment for preparing and cooking food [300199784], culinary equipment [300199765], equipment by context [300239170], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Strainers through which tea, or sometimes coffee, is poured in order to catch the loose leaves or grounds. For culinary tools which enclose tea leaves, or sometimes coffee grounds, within a cup or pot of water while the beverage brews, use "tea infusers."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filtro a través del cual el té, o a veces el café, es vertido para coger las hojas sueltas o los posos. Para instrumentos culinarios que encierran hojas de té, o a veces grano de café, dentro de una taza u olla de agua mientras la bebida se hace infusión, use "infusor para té”.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Filters waardoor thee of soms ook koffie wordt geschonken met de bedoeling dat het de losse blaadjes of het bezinksel opvangt. Gebruik 'thee-eieren' voor keukengerei dat theeblaadjes of soms gemalen koffie bevat en in een kop of pot met water wordt gedaan zodat het kan trekken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052470/Molen, Zilver (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sieb, durch das Tee und manchmal Kaffee gegossen wird, um die losen Blätter oder Sätze aufzufangen. Für ein Küchengerät, das die Teeblätter oder mitunter den Kaffesatz enthält und in einer Tasse oder Kanne mit Wasser liegt, während das Getränk aufgebrüht wird, siehe "Tee-Ei".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>茶或咖啡倒進此濾器後，鬆散的茶葉或渣滓會留在濾器裡面。將茶葉或是咖啡渣包起，置於水杯或水壺裡煮泡的廚房器具，則稱為「浸出器」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
